subsection.p:
From our conversion factor we also learn that 
    \blert{ 1~\text{radian} = \dfrac{180\degree}{\pi} \approx 57.3\degree}
  So while 1\degree is a relatively small angle, 1 radian is much larger â€” nearly 60\degree, in fact. 
    circle

